THE STUDENT PILOT REPORTED HE WAS PRACTICING TOUCH-AND-GO TAKEOFFS AND 
LANDINGS ON RUNWAY 11. WHILE ROLLING AFTER THE 4TH LANDING, POWER WAS 
APPLIED FOR TAKEOFF. AT ABOUT THAT TIME, THE AIRCRAFT VEERED TO THE LEFT AND 
RAN OFF THE RUNWAY. SUBSEQUENTLY, IT STRUCK A DRAINAGE DITCH AND THE NOSE 
GEAR FAILED. THE AIRCRAFT BECAME AIRBORNE MOMENTARILY, TOUCHED DOWN AND 
NOSED OVER. 
